Eupafolin suppresses TGF-&#x03b2;1-induced human lung fibroblasts differentiation by downregulating &#x03b2;-catenin/plasminogen activator inhibitor-1 signaling</ce:title><ce:author-group id="aut0001"><ce:author id="au0001" author-id="S2667142522000173-4d4db3a05a082a29de1f62b08aaa6d29"><ce:given-name>Mei</ce:given-name><ce:surname>Zhu</ce:surname><ce:cross-ref refid="fn1"><ce:sup loc="post">1</ce:sup></ce:cross-ref></ce:author><ce:author id="au0002" author-id="S2667142522000173-62114f3fc3878a1659d44527f38ccf3b"><ce:given-name>Jian</ce:given-name><ce:surname>Zhang</ce:surname><ce:cross-ref refid="fn1"><ce:sup loc="post">1</ce:sup></ce:cross-ref></ce:author><ce:author id="au0003" author-id="S2667142522000173-8951b43f3d2d92bdbb4c387d9e3d7e78"><ce:given-name>Xionghua</ce:given-name><ce:surname>Sun</ce:surname><ce:cross-ref refid="cor0001"><ce:sup loc="post">&#x204e;</ce:sup></ce:cross-ref><ce:e-address id="ead0001" type="email" xlink:href="mailto:sunxionghua@suda.edu.cn">sunxionghua@suda.edu.cn</ce:e-address></ce:author><ce:author id="au0004" author-id="S2667142522000173-9541226e05f5dbe81a22485861bcc2ff"><ce:given-name>Xihua</ce:given-name><ce:surname>Chen</ce:surname></ce:author><ce:author id="au0005" author-id="S2667142522000173-496b8af7e9f0268e55bfa7b32e38d759"><ce:given-name>Xiaogang</ce:given-name><ce:surname>Jiang</ce:surname><ce:cross-ref refid="cor0001"><ce:sup loc="post">&#x204e;</ce:sup></ce:cross-ref><ce:e-address id="ead0002" type="email" xlink:href="mailto:jiangxiaogang@suda.edu.cn">jiangxiaogang@suda.edu.cn</ce:e-address></ce:author><ce:affiliation id="aff0001" affiliation-id="S2667142522000173-228054aff2760967711849d2ce889ced"><ce:textfn id="cetextfn0001">College of Pharmaceutical Sciences, Soochow University, 199 Renai Road, Suzhou 215123, China</ce:textfn><sa:affiliation><sa:organization>College of Pharmaceutical Sciences</sa:organization><sa:organization>Soochow University</sa:organization><sa:address-line>199 Renai Road</sa:address-line><sa:city>Suzhou</sa:city><sa:postal-code>215123</sa:postal-code><sa:country>China</sa:country></sa:affiliation><ce:source-text id="staff0001">College of Pharmaceutical Sciences, Soochow University, 199 Renai Road, Suzhou 215123, China</ce:source-text></ce:affiliation><ce:correspondence id="cor0001"><ce:label>&#x204e;</ce:label><ce:text id="cetext0001">Corresponding authors.</ce:text></ce:correspondence><ce:footnote id="fn1"><ce:label>1</ce:label><ce:note-para id="notep0001" view="all">These authors contributed equally to this work.</ce:note-para></ce:footnote></ce:author-group><ce:date-received day="23" month="10" year="2021"/><ce:date-revised day="24" month="12" year="2021"/><ce:date-accepted day="25" month="1" year="2022"/><ce:abstract id="abs0001" class="author-highlights" view="all"><ce:section-title id="cesectitle0001">Highlights</ce:section-title><ce:abstract-sec id="abss0001" view="all"><ce:simple-para id="spara010" view="all"><ce:list id="celist0001"><ce:list-item id="celistitem0001"><ce:label>&#x2022;</ce:label><ce:para id="para0002" view="all">Flavones from <ce:italic>EL</ce:italic> exerted a stronger anti-fibrotic activity than flavonols.</ce:para></ce:list-item><ce:list-item id="celistitem0002"><ce:label>&#x2022;</ce:label><ce:para id="para0003" view="all">Eupafolin presented the highest activity among eight flavonoids from <ce:italic>EL</ce:italic>.</ce:para></ce:list-item><ce:list-item id="celistitem0003"><ce:label>&#x2022;</ce:label><ce:para id="para0004" view="all">Eupafolin suppressed lung fibroblast-to-myofibroblast differentiation.</ce:para></ce:list-item><ce:list-item id="celistitem0004"><ce:label>&#x2022;</ce:label><ce:para id="para0005" view="all">Classical TGF-&#x03b2;/Smad2/3 was not involved in eupafolin action.</ce:para></ce:list-item><ce:list-item id="celistitem0005"><ce:label>&#x2022;</ce:label><ce:para id="para0006" view="all">Eupafolin-suppressive effect was by downregulating &#x03b2;-catenin/PAI-1.</ce:para></ce:list-item></ce:list></ce:simple-para></ce:abstract-sec></ce:abstract><ce:abstract id="abs0002" view="all" class="author"><ce:section-title id="cesectitle0002">Abstract</ce:section-title><ce:abstract-sec id="abss0002" view="all"><ce:simple-para id="spara011" view="all">The anti-fibrotic activity of flavonoids from <ce:italic>Eupatorium lindleyanum DC</ce:italic> (<ce:italic>EL</ce:italic>) remains unclear. Our results showed that flavones from the plant exerted a stronger inhibitory effect than flavonols, and eupafolin presented the highest activity on lung fibroblast differentiation. Eupafolin weakened the levels of &#x03b1;-smooth muscle actin, the production of type I collagen and fibronectin, fibroblast-containing gel contractility and microfilament formation in transforming growth factor-&#x03b2;1-induced lung fibroblasts. Interestingly, eupafolin did not affect the canonical TGF-&#x03b2;/Smad2/3 pathway. Eupafolin reduced the levels of plasminogen activator inhibitor-1 (PAI-1), and pharmacological inhibition and knockdown of PAI-1 mitigated the differentiation of lung fibroblasts. Finally, &#x03b2;-catenin agonist, SKL2001, reversed the suppressive effect of eupafolin on PAI-1 expression and lung fibroblast differentiation. Therefore, flavones have higher anti-fibrotic activity than flavonols obtained from <ce:italic>EL</ce:italic>, and eupafolin suppressed lung fibroblast differentiation by downregulating &#x03b2;-catenin/PAI-1 signaling rather than the canonical TGF-&#x03b2;/Smad2/3 pathway.</ce:simple-para></ce:abstract-sec></ce:abstract><ce:abstract id="abs0003" class="graphical" view="all"><ce:section-title id="cesectitle0003">Graphical abstract</ce:section-title><ce:abstract-sec id="abss0003" view="all"><ce:simple-para id="spara012" view="all"> [Display omitted] </ce:simple-para></ce:abstract-sec></ce:abstract><ce:keywords id="keys0001" view="all" class="keyword"><ce:section-title id="cesectitle0004">Keywords</ce:section-title><ce:keyword id="key0001"><ce:text id="cetext0002"><ce:italic>Eupatorium lindleyanum DC</ce:italic></ce:text></ce:keyword><ce:keyword id="key0002"><ce:text id="cetext0003">Flavonoids</ce:text></ce:keyword><ce:keyword id="key0003"><ce:text id="cetext0004">Eupafolin</ce:text></ce:keyword><ce:keyword id="key0004"><ce:text id="cetext0005">Fibroblast differentiation</ce:text></ce:keyword><ce:keyword id="key0005"><ce:text id="cetext0006">Pulmonary fibrosis</ce:text></ce:keyword><ce:keyword id="key0006"><ce:text id="cetext0007">Plasminogen activator inhibitor-1</ce:text></ce:keyword></ce:keywords><ce:keywords id="keys0002" class="abr" view="all"><ce:section-title id="cesectitle0005">Abbreviations</ce:section-title><ce:keyword id="key0007"><ce:text id="cetext0008"><ce:italic>EL</ce:italic></ce:text><ce:keyword id="key8a"><ce:text id="cetext8a"><ce:italic>Eupatorium lindleyanum DC</ce:italic></ce:text></ce:keyword></ce:keyword><ce:keyword id="key0008"><ce:text id="cetext0009">&#x03b1;-SMA</ce:text><ce:keyword id="key9a"><ce:text id="cetext9a">&#x03b1;-smooth muscle actin</ce:text></ce:keyword></ce:keyword><ce:keyword id="key0009"><ce:text id="cetext0010">TGF-&#x03b2;1</ce:text><ce:keyword id="key10a"><ce:text id="cetext10a">transforming growth factor &#x03b2;1</ce:text></ce:keyword></ce:keyword><ce:keyword id="key0010"><ce:text id="cetext0011">PAI-1</ce:text><ce:keyword id="key11a"><ce:text id="cetext11a">plasminogen activator inhibitor-1</ce:text></ce:keyword></ce:keyword><ce:keyword id="key0011"><ce:text id="cetext0012">siRNA</ce:text><ce:keyword id="key12a"><ce:text id="cetext12a">small interference RNA</ce:text></ce:keyword></ce:keyword><ce:keyword id="key0012"><ce:text id="cetext0013">ECM</ce:text><ce:keyword id="key13a"><ce:text id="cetext13a">extracellular matrix</ce:text></ce:keyword></ce:keyword></ce:keywords></ja:head></ja:article></doc:document>
